Description:
High end quality in affordable locale.
This charming, freshly renovated two bedroom home will sure tick all the right boxes. Perfectly positioned with street frontage on a block of just two dwellings, it is close to Westfield Airport West, local cafes and public transport which all add to the lifestyle on offer here. Sliding doors open up the lounge area to a lovely fire pit and built in seating area in the front yard making it perfect for entertaining. A sleek kitchen includes gas cooktop, dishwasher, ample storage, dining space and separate study. Two large bedrooms with built in robes share a central bathroom with the addition of a second toilet. Highlighted with polished floors, split system and rear north facing courtyard. The hard work has been done, the charm is immediate, the location perfect. Whether its your first home, somewhere to downsize to or to be an investment, you cant go wrong.
Online Auction Link: https://anywhereauctions.com.au/app/property?propertyId=1948
Please note during Victorian Government Stage 4 COVID-19 Restrictions a physical inspection of property is prohibited. We welcome your enquiry to discuss this property in more detail.

Description:
Space, Serenity And Lifestyle
Due to Melbourne's Stage 4 restrictions, the Brad Teal team is working from home and is available via mobile, direct lines, email and even virtually. As private inspections are not currently permitted, please contact our team to discuss your options to view this property virtually.
A picture of family pride, this considerably spacious six bedroom, three bathroom residence is set in a quiet, neighbourly court close to schools, parks, Keilor Central shops, buses and freeways. Renovated and extended over time, a generous layout presents large open living, dining zones and modern kitchen flowing to an undercover alfresco entertainment area and sundrenched backyard featuring heated above-ground pool with timber decking. In addition, a second living area/bedroom also enjoys direct access to the backyard. An all gas kitchen impresses with stone counters, 900mm stainless steel cooker and plentiful storage options. Spread over two levels are six bedrooms most with built-in-robes. The downstairs master boasts ensuite, while two remodelled bathrooms serve subsequent bedrooms. A long list of extras includes ducted heating, split-system air conditioner, evaporative cooling, ceiling fans, solar electricity, CCTV/alarm, electric shutters, storage, double carport plus automated access to additional undercover parking and huge triple car garage providing secure storage for boats, recreational vehicles, trailers and much more.

Description:
UNDER CONTRACT
More than meets the eye, this single-level home benefits from an extended floorplan providing a family lifestyle of immediate quality and versatility along with future potential to enhance or subdivide (STCA) - all with instant access to Centreway's array of shops and popular eateries.
A neat interior comprises a central hallway and three generous bedrooms complemented by a central renovated bathroom.
Multiple living areas include a front lounge room and a rear family room that is serviced by an updated kitchen with 900mm stove, dishwasher and family sized meals area.
Highlights include hydronic heating, polished floorboards, large laundry plus a spacious backyard with oversized carport via wide side driveway and two handy storage sheds.
A short stroll to the bus stop (on Milleara Road), it's also close to a range of quality schools (including PEGS, Keilor Heights Primary School and St Bernard's College) as well as quick and easy access to the Calder Freeway.
Inspection by Appointment Only.
DAVID GIGLIOTTI 0411 824 854
*** COVID-19 Announcement *** If you're attending an inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance.

Description:
Elegant Family Home in Premium Position
A serene cul-de-sac is the perfect setting for this grand two storey residence of generous proportions defined by enchanting indoor-outdoor spaces and luxurious furnishings, a fitting complement to the domain's enviable lifestyle. Thoughtful design provides a marvelous balance of multiple living areas allowing the whole family to relax in harmony or privately according to their needs, all in ideal proximity to schools and shops. A gracious entrance hallway introduces formal lounge and dining displaying ornate ceiling roses, crystal chandeliers and granite mantel surrounding an electric log fireplace. The extensive family and meals zone presiding over the lush rear garden adjoins the granite-benched kitchen housing quality stainless-steel appliances. A smart home office and downstairs bathroom complete the lower floor. The upper level consists of a spacious living area with soft carpet underfoot, an amazing master suite hosting parents retreat, walk-in-robe and twin-vanity, spa bath ensuite with separate toilet and three further double robed bedrooms share a lovely main bathroom. Enjoy the outdoors and barbeques on a sheltered alfresco patio made for entertaining. Features include ducted heating/cooling, alarm, shed and double auto garage with internal entry.
Meticulously maintained and well situated to reserves, schools, Overnewton Anglican College, public transport, amazing Taylors Lakes and Watergardens Shopping Centres and has easy access to Calder Freeway.
To view the due diligence checklist for home and residential property buyers copy link https://www.consumer.vic.gov.au/duediligencechecklist.

UNDER CONSTRUCTION TOWNHOUSES IN GROWTH AREA
Opportunity to buy a stunning modern townhouse due for completion early 2021 in the growth area of St Albans. Choice of two:

Close to shops and public transport, these stunning modern townhouses are affordable for the first home buyer or savvy investor. Comprising of living room, spacious well equiped kitchen and dining area opening to private open space, down stairs powder room, bedrooms with BIR's, bathroom (one with ensuite), and laundry completes these beautiful homes. Located close to schools and within walking distance to St Alban's shopping center and restaurant strip, and with St Albans and Keilor Plains train stations being within walking distance or a just 3 minute drive, these properties are not to be missed.
Secure your home in one of Melbourne's growth centers now.

https://auctionslive.com/app/bidder-registration/Rrbe
Once in a while, a house comes onto the market that ticks all the boxes. As you step into this lavish home you can't help but be impressed by its perfect presentation, open floor plan and ability to entertain family and friends. Comprising of 4 good size bedrooms, master with ensuite and its own private courtyard, plus study/5th bedroom. A superb open formal lounge area is adjacent to a separate dining area. The spacious solid timber kitchen with ample bench space overlooks a large meals area, that flows seamlessly to a large rumpus/theatre room highlighted by raked ceiling and a built-in bar. The meals area steps out to a fantastic undercover paved pergola area ideal for entertaining. The extra-large 2-car garage/ workshop with rear access finishes this impressive package.

Lifestyle Ease, Space And Convenience
With the health and well-being of our community being front of mind we have additional measures in place at all property inspections. Our COVID-19 conditions of entry are available for your viewing click here: https://go.aws/2Z5oMmV
Enjoy light filled ambience and contemporary comforts in this spacious three bedroom single level residence nestled in a peaceful, yet convenient pocket of sought after Niddrie. Thoughtfully updated, this home impresses with its large living flooded in natural light featuring gas log fireplace, high ceilings and polished floorboards. Towards the rear, a generous undercover entertaining deck flows from renovated open kitchen/dining zones displaying stone top benches, quality appliances, dishwasher and abundant custom-built storage including large pantry. Designed for a low maintenance lifestyle, it includes three robed double bedrooms served by central family bathroom and modern laundry with extra storage and convenience of a separate toilet. Plus, hallway storage, ducted heating, split-system air conditioner, ceiling fans, fully fenced surrounds and remote controlled roller door entrance to secure off street parking and private backyard. Excellent access to walking/cycle paths, Penleigh and Essendon Grammar, primary schools, freeways and the M80, with buses to Keilor Road shopping and café precinct just around the corner.

Luxurious House seated on 624 m2 Rectangular Block near to Keilor Plains Station
The impressive nature of this elegantly perched single-levelled home is evident from the outset. Enhanced over 624sqm of land, its grandeur facade is the beginning of its stunning interior arrangement that exudes practicality and versatility for everyday living with space for the growing family. Soaring 9 foot ceilings throughout, it offers a formal lounge upon entry, hardwood timber kitchen with granite bench tops overlooking a sun soaked meals & family area thereon to a large rumpus with a second kitchen. The sleeping quarters consist of 4 generous sized bedrooms, master with a walk in robe and ensuite, others with mirrored built in robes and serviced by the main bathroom providing the ultimate level of privacy and comfort for all occupants.
KEY FEATURES:
• Quality hardwood kitchen with granite bench top

• Minutes away from Keilor plain train station, St Albans primary school, St Albans
North Primary school, shopping centres and parks
Look no further, this one ticks all the home and lifestyle options!

Description:
Family Favourite with Exceptional Corner Credentials
Please register your interest in this property so that we can ensure you are included in the Virtual Auction and/or contacted in the event the property is going to be sold prior to the Virtual Auction 14 August at 1pm
*** This property is available for inspection by appointment - Please contact us to arrange a suitable time ***
In one of Keilor East's most popular pockets, this classic triple-fronted sixties' home provides an immediately functional family environment while offering a myriad of opportunities to rebuild or possibly redevelop (STCA) taking advantage of its prominent corner position. Well-presented interior currently comprises three bedrooms (large master) all with built-in robes, study, neat family bathroom with floor-to-ceiling tiles and separate WC. Add to this a central lounge and dining leading through to the spotless kitchen with solid timber cabinetry and adjoining meals area. Along with ducted heating, air conditioner (dining area) and motorized security shutters, the home also includes a sizeable backyard with paved undercover patio, spacious workshop/storeroom complete with kitchenette and laundry facilities, plus an oversized single garage (remote-control) accessed via Ash Grove. Walking distance to the open spaces of Rosehill Park, Phillip Road/Buckley Street buses and Milleara Shopping Centre, it's also close to popular primary and secondary schools (including PEGS and St Bernard's College), as well as easy freeway access.
*** COVID-19 ANNOUNCEMENT ***
If you're attending a Private Appointment, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from our team members, and if requested wait outside until the property is ready for the appointment. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance. Thank you.

Description:
Easy-Living Excellence with Quiet Convenience
*Due to Melbourne's Stage 4 Restrictions, all Nelson Alexander team members are working from home. Please contact us via email or phone to speak about your options to view this property virtually. Thank you.*
A brilliant entry into Niddrie, rewarding investment or downsize opportunity, this charming mid-century home is perfect either way with its generous floorplan, quality enhancements and immaculate low-maintenance surrounds. Filled with natural light, the home's impeccable interior comprises three genuinely large bedrooms (two with built-in robes) complemented by two updated bathrooms (one with laundry facilities). Adding to its appeal is an open-plan living/meals area accompanied by a well-appointed kitchen complete with tiled splashbacks, ample cupboard space, stainless steel cooking appliances and dishwasher. Other highlights of this impressive home include ducted heating, evaporative cooling and three additional split-system air conditioners, along with solar power, solid hardwood floors and external sun blinds. Double doors from the living area reveal a fabulous al-fresco style entertaining deck and wonderfully private back garden with handy storeroom/workshop, plus under-house storage, front irrigation system and the added advantage of a tandem double carport. Bus stop around the corner and walking distance to Steele Creek trails and acres of parkland, it's also close to Keilor Road trams and vibrant cafe/retail precinct, popular primary and secondary schools, as well as quick and easy freeway access.

Single-Level Sensation in the Best Location!
*Due to Melbourne's Stage 4 Restrictions, all Nelson Alexander team members are working from home. Please contact us via email or phone to speak about your options to view this property virtually. Thank you.*
Unit 2 & 4 NOW SOLD - ONLY 1 remaining!!
Brand-new and ready to simply move in and enjoy, this brilliant rear villa presents a lifestyle opportunity of low-maintenance perfection with its intelligent design, quality inclusions and premier position in a sought-after Niddrie-edge neighbourhood. Every room filled with natural light, the free-flowing interior showcases two bedrooms (larger master) both with mirrored robes, along with a stylish central bathroom complete with separate shower and bathtub. The versatility of the open-plan living/dining area is matched by the quality of the kitchen boasting stone benchtops and island breakfast bar, soft-close drawers and Technika appliances (dishwasher, oven and gas cooktop). Other stand-out features include split-system heating and cooling (living area and both bedrooms), square-set ceilings with efficient LED lighting, quality carpets and engineered floors, concealed laundry facilities and double-glazed windows all-round. Step outside to discover a wonderfully wide rear courtyard plus the added appeal of a remote-control garage with internal entry. A short stroll to Matthews Avenue trams, Keilor Road's renowned cafes, restaurants and retail precinct, close to primary and secondary schools, as well as easy access to Essendon Fields Shopping Centre and the Tullamarine Freeway/Citylink.
